ssed": true}, "short_span_min_tokens": {"details": {"min_tokens": 2, "token_count": 134}, "passed": true}}, "text": "5. RUMORED PURGE OF NUMBER-TWO CHINESE COMMUNIST LEADER\n\nChinese Nationalist newspapers have begun speculating that Liu Shao-chi, Mao Tse-tung's principal lieutenant in the Chinese Communist hierarchy since 1945, has been purged.\n\nnoting Liu's absence from public functions since 5 August, surmise that the purge will be announced at the 8th Congress of the Chinese Communist Party, scheduled to open in Peiping on 15 September.\n\nManeuvering among Mao's lieutenants for the top positions in a \"collective leadership\" may well have begun, and there is an outside chance that Liu has already lost out. His five-week absence, however, is not excessively long for a Chinese Communist official. It can logically be explained by the press of business immediately prior to the opening of the party congress, in which he is expected to play a major role", "token_count": 134, "token_end_0based": 133, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "5 rumored purge of number-two chinese communist leader chinese nationalist newspapers have begun speculating that liu shao-chi mao tse-tung's principal lieutenant in the chinese communist hierarchy since 1945 has been purged noting liu's absence from public functions since 5 august surmise that the purge will be announced at the 8th congress of the chinese communist party scheduled to open in peiping on 15 september maneuvering among mao's lieutenants for the top positions in a collective leadership may well have begun and there is an outside chance that liu has already lost out his five-week absence however is not excessively long for a chinese communist official it can logically be explained by the press of business immediately prior to the opening of the party congress in which he is expected to play a major role", "unred_source_page": 8}
